This drags its feet in circles without going anywhere. The table is both purposeless and unfunny because the jokes are rote and expected, and the D-class comments are like one guy loudly laughing at the comedy set after every joke. The rest of the article relies on having the rest of the Donkman context like a bike relies on its wheels; it has no purpose or movement without it. It takes a thousand-odd words to reveal a dead donkey, as it were, being clubbed like a Canadian seal.







