There are two main approaches I've seen to articles that work well within a canon: those that actively try to further the story, and those that try to remain completely independent of the story but exist in the same universe. This tries to do both and thus falls flat on its face. Besides a lot of small issues that took me out of the experience1, the core story here is extremely contrived and the characters are even more unrealistic. Aloysius talks like a Saturday-morning cartoon villain, so him casually murdering Mr. Thompson had no effect on me besides a slight chuckle at the absurdity of the entire situation.

This is a -1 from me.

Footnotes
1. Why is the Discovery log not just collapsed into the Investigation log? Why are descriptions of the evidence gathered available to Level-2 Researchers, but can only be physically interacted with by Level-3 Researchers? If they're not able to interact or test them, then there's no point to even having them know it exists.








